
create the rhel8.0.repo in /etc/yum.repos.d
- just copy the contents of the file from
  https://gitlab.cee.redhat.com/thozza/rhel-8-useful-scripts/blob/master/rhel-8.0.repo

- must install
  . python-pyyaml
  . jinja2
  . python3-unicodecsv

- Clone the rhel8 scripts repo and put it in your path.

$ git -c http.sslVerify=false clone https://gitlab.cee.redhat.com/thozza/rhel-8-useful-scripts.git
Cloning into 'rhel-8-useful-scripts'...
remote: Counting objects: 74, done.
remote: Compressing objects: 100% (42/42), done.
remote: Total 74 (delta 37), reused 59 (delta 31)
Unpacking objects: 100% (74/74), done.

$ mv rhel-8-useful-scripts/ rhel8

PATH=$PATH:$HOME/rhel8



